PREVIOUSLY ON
"THE SUITE LIFE ON DECK"...

I WANTED TO GO
BACK TO KETTLECORN

FOR MY GRAMMY PICKETT'S
90th BIRTHDAY.

WHAT IF I TAKE YOU
TO VISIT GRAMMY PICKLE?

- BAILEY MOVED BACK
 TO KETTLECORN.
- WHAT?!

- ( groans )
- ( screams )

- BAILEY, ARE YOU THERE?
- ( phone beeping )

HELLO?
BAILEY?
HELLO?

- ( snoring )
- HELLO?

- GRAMMY PICKETT.
- ( snorts )

OH WELL, AT LEAST
YOU'RE ALIVE.

WELL, HEY THERE.
WHAT CAN I DO YOU FOR?

OH, HI THERE, MR. PICKETT.
I'M CODY, BAILEY'S FRIEND FROM--
( slams )

Woman:
WHAT IS ALL THAT
RUCKUS OUT THERE?

Mr. Pickett:
IT'S THAT SCRAWNY KID
WHO BROKE OUR BAILEY'S HEART.

CODY!
IT IS SO NICE TO FINALLY
MEET YOU IN PERSON.

OH, JEEPERS,
YOU ARE BONY.

THAT IS LIKE HUGGING
A BAG OF TWIGS.

- CLYDE, COME FEEL HIM.
- I'LL PASS.
OH, YOU.

LOOK, I'M HERE BECAUSE
I'M WORRIED ABOUT BAILEY.

SHE LEFT YESTERDAY TO COME
SURPRISE GRAMMY PICKETT
FOR HER 90th BIRTHDAY.
BUT WHEN I CALLED HER

SHE SOUNDED
LIKE SHE WAS IN DANGER.
SHE'S HERE, RIGHT?

- NO.
- MY POOR BABY.

WELL, I HOPE
SHE'S NOT HURT.

( snores )
OW.
THAT HURT.

WAKE UP.  CHECK TO SEE
IF THE CORN GOBLIN
IS STILL THERE.

- WHY DO I HAVE TO DO IT?
- BECAUSE--

IF YOUR FACE
IS THE FIRST THING
IT SEES IN THE MORNING,
IT'LL SCARE HIM OFF.
OKAY, WE'LL DO IT TOGETHER.

- ON THREE--
- WAIT WAIT WAIT WAIT!

- DOES THREE COME
 BEFORE OR AFTER--
- ON GO!

- READY?
- UH-HUH.
SET, GO!
( screaming )

IT'S JUST A SCARECROW.
WOULD YOU LET GO?

IT'S NOT THE CORN GOBLIN.
IT'S JUST A SCARECROW.

THE WIND MUST HAVE
BLOWN IT OVER FROM
THE CORNFIELD LAST NIGHT.

I HATE THIS STUPID
CORN COUNTRY!

- MIGHT AS WELL START WALKING.
- WALKING?!

WELL, CAN YOU JUST
PULL ME IN THE TRUCK?

WHAT DO I LOOK LIKE, AN OX?
DON'T ANSWER THAT!

JUST COME ON.
AND WATCH OUT
FOR CORN BEETLES.

OH LOOK,
YOU FOOLED ME ONCE.

I'M NOT GOING TO FALL FOR
ANOTHER PRETEND CORN CREATURE.
( buzzing )
( shrieking )
( screams )

- KETTLECORN'S THE OTHER WAY.
- ( screaming continues )
♪ OH AY OH, OH AY OH ♪
♪ COME ALONG WITH ME ♪
♪ AND LET'S HEAD OUT TO SEE ♪
♪ WHAT THIS WORLD HAS ♪
♪ FOR YOU AND FOR ME NOW ♪

♪ WHICHEVER WAY
THE WIND BLOWS ♪

- ♪ WE SAY... ♪
- ♪ HEY-HO, LET'S GO! ♪

-  ♪ OH AY OH ♪ 
-  ♪ THIS BOAT'S ROCKING ♪

-  ♪ OH AY OH ♪ 
-  ♪ AIN'T NO STOPPING US NOW ♪

♪ 'CAUSE WE'RE LIVING
THE SUITE LIFE ♪

-  ♪ OH AY OH ♪ 
-  ♪ THIS BOAT'S ROCKING ♪

-  ♪ OH AY OH ♪ 
-  ♪ ROCKING THE WHOLE
WORLD ROUND ♪

♪ AND WE'RE LIVING
THE SUITE LIFE NOW ♪
♪ HEY HO!  OH AY OH ♪
♪ LET'S GO! ♪

OH, WOODY, I STILL NEED MONEY
FOR MAYA'S ANNIVERSARY GIFT.

- CAN YOU SPOT ME A 20?
- ARE YOU KIDDING?

I DON'T EVEN HAVE QUARTERS
TO DO LAUNDRY.

YOU DO LAUNDRY?
SO IT'S NOT YOUR CLOTHES
THAT SMELL?

BUT WE'VE BEEN PLANNING
THIS FAMILY REUNION
FOR OVER A YEAR.

I'M EXTREMELY SORRY
FOR THE MIX-UP, MR. EVERHART,

- BUT WE'RE COMPLETELY BOOKED.
- GREAT.  PERFECT.

WHY DON'T YOU GO TELL
MY WIFE, BECAUSE I'M
NOT TELLING HER.
OH.
THAT'S A WOMAN?!
I MEAN...
THAT'S A WOMAN!
I'LL SEE WHAT I CAN DO.

- I WILL PAY ANYTHING!
- DID YOU HEAR THAT?
HE'LL PAY ANYTHING.

HAVE A SEAT HERE.
ZACK, PLEASE, GIVE MR. EVERHART
WHATEVER HE WANTS.
ALL RIGHTY.

YOU KNOW, MR. EVERHART,
TODAY IS YOUR LUCKY DAY.
MY WIFE FELL OVERBOARD?

WOW.
NO, I THINK WE WOULD
HAVE HEARD THE SPLASH.

WELCOME TO YOUR TROPICAL
SUITE, MR. EVERHART.

I HOPE YOU AND YOUR WIFE
WILL BE COMFORTABLE HERE.

OH, FEEL FREE TO PUSH
THESE BEDS TOGETHER.
OR FARTHER APART.

HOW DID YOU EVER
FIND US A ROOM?

I JUST MOVED
A FEW THINGS AROUND.

AH, YOU CERTAINLY ARE MORE
HELPFUL THAN THAT OTHER MANAGER.

OH, AND PLUS HE
HAS ANGER ISSUES.

THIS ONE TIME THIS GUEST
ASKED FOR AN EXTRA TOWEL,

- HE BIT HIS EAR CLEAN OFF.
- OH!

- I'D STAY AWAY FROM HIM
 IF I WERE YOU.
- OKAY.
( grunts, panting )
WHAT IS IN HERE?!
MY WIFE'S SWIMWEAR.

HOW MANY BATHING SUITS
DOES SHE HAVE?
JUST THE ONE.

WHAT EXACTLY
DID YOU DO TO BREAK
MY LITTLE GIRL'S HEART?

( stammers )
I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

EUNICE, HAVE YOU HEARD
FROM THE POLICE?

NO, NOT YET.
I LEFT SHERIFF BOB
A MESSAGE,

BUT HE'S PROBABLY STILL
OUT DELIVERING THE MAIL.
( shrieking )

All:
BAILEY!

- OH.
- OH DAD.

- CODY.

SUCH GOOD TIME.

LONGER THAN WE THOUGHT,

I WAS ATTACKED
BY A GIANT CORN BEETLE.

EVERYBODY,
THIS IS LONDON.

- LOOK AT THIS WELT.

JUST RUB SOME MUD ON IT.
O-OKAY.

BAILEY, I'VE MISSED YOU
SO MUCH.

IF YOU WERE DEAD OR ALIVE.

WELL, I'M ALIVE.
THANKS FOR COMING.

( whimpers )

AW, HONEY, I HATE
TO BREAK IT TO YOU--
THAT AIN'T MUD.
EWWW.
EW, STUPID CORN COUNTRY.
WHOA, BAILEY, WAIT.

NOW THAT I'M HERE,
THERE'S SOMETHING
I HAVE TO TELL YOU.

- I WANT YOU TO--
- HEY, Y'ALL!

- MOOSE!
- GOOD TO SEE YOU,
  MR. PICKETT.

OH, COME ON NOW.
HOW MANY TIMES DO I
HAVE TO TELL YOU?

- CALL ME CLYDE.
- ( grunts )

BAILEY, LOOK WHO'S HERE.
GIVE MOOSE A HUG.

- ( forced laugh )
- OH, BAILEY, I CAN'T
 BELIEVE YOU'RE HOME.

- I MISSED YOU SO MUCH.
- I MISSED YOU TOO, MOOSE.

I DIDN'T EXPECT
YOU TO BE HERE.
NEITHER DID I.

YOU KNOW I WOULD NEVER
MISS GRAMMY PICKETT'S
SURPRISE PARTY.

- IT'S NOT A PARTY
 TILL MOOSE IS HERE.
- YAY.

GIRLS, COME AND HELP ME PUT
THE CANDLES ON GRAMMY'S CAKE.

- ( snores )
- EVEN WITH THE THREE OF US,
IT'S GONNA TAKE AWHILE.

YOU SURE YOU DON'T
WANT TO GO HELP DECORATE
WITH THE REST OF THE GIRLS?

NO, I'D MUCH RATHER
HANG OUT WITH YOU GUYS.

IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU,
LITTLE FELLER.
DID YOU GET SMALLER?
YES, I DID SLIM DOWN.

I RECENTLY BECAME
A PESCETARIAN.

IT'S A GOOD THING YOU'RE
A MAN OF FAITH, 'CAUSE YOU'RE
LOOKING A LITTLE SICKLY.

YEAH, MOOSE, WHEN YOU

WOODY, WOODY,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

CARRYING MRS. EVERHART'S
TUBE TOP,
AND HER NIGHTIE.

WELL, WHEN YOU'RE DONE HERE,

TO YOUR CABIN.

- GRANDPA EVERHART

YOU RENTED OUT MY ROOM?
WHERE AM I SUPPOSED TO SLEEP?

DON'T WORRY.
I'VE UPGRADED YOU
TO THE LINEN SUITE.

MAYBE.

NOW LET'S GO, LET'S GO.
COME ON.
YOU KNOW, WOODY,
THESE BAGS HAVE WHEELS.
DANG IT!

YOU SURE LOOK PRETTY
WHEN YOU SHUCK CORN.
AW, SHUCKS.

IT'S JUST NICE AND PEACEFUL
BEING BACK ON THE FARM.

-  ( chickens cluck )

OH!

THOSE CHICKENS ARE VICIOUS!

BUT NOT ANYMORE!

OH, LONDON, YOU'RE WHITTLING.

 ALL YOU PEOPLE WITH.

USE THE KNIFE?

IS THERE SOME SORT

THE TRICK IS
HAVING MUSCLES, SON.

MR. PICKETT.

TOUCHE.
